---
// Vision register, placed low on Home so it doesn't compete with the problem
// hook. "Foundational data for foundational models" + the single-cell RNA-seq
// analogy. Shape only — never a magnitude (Rule 2). Future tense on prediction.
---

<section class="border-t border-line/60 px-6 py-20 md:px-10 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[72rem]">
    <p
      class="rise font-button text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent-700"
    >
      The data frontier
    </p>
    <div
      class="mt-5 grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[1.1fr_1fr] md:gap-16"
    >
      <h2
        class="rise text-balance font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink md:text-[2.5rem]"
      >
        Foundational data for the next generation of models.
      </h2>
      <div
        class="rise space-y-4 self-end text-lg leading-[1.7] text-muted"
        style="animation-delay: 100ms"
      >
        <p>
          Charged-tRNA supply under production load has structure — a shared
          stress component and a protein-specific component — that no method
          could measure until now. This category of data didn't exist before.
        </p>
        <p>
          A decade ago, single-cell RNA-seq revealed structure in cellular state
          that no one could see before, and a generation of models was built on
          it. Measured tRNA supply is that kind of data for protein expression —
          the foundation that predictable expression will be built on.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
